parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug failure can cause the engine to misfire, leading to a loss of power, hesitation, and vibration, which can increase the risk of an accident or leave the driver stranded.
Oil pan leaks can cause the engine to lose oil, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a fire, which can increase the risk of an accident or injury.
Crank position sensor failure can cause the engine to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident or leaving the driver stranded.
Exhaust manifold failure can cause an exhaust leak, leading to a loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing a fire, which can increase the risk of an accident or injury.
Turbocharger failure can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of acceleration, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing an accident or leaving the driver stranded.
Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: transmission grinds or makes loud noises
